# .dockerignore — minimize the build context sent to the Docker daemon.
#
# The Dockerfile does `COPY . .` into the builder. Without this file the entire
# working directory (VCS history, planning notes, coverage artifacts, docs, CI
# config, deploy assets, and any local-only working material) is shipped into the
# build context and baked into the builder layer — slow, and it pulls in files
# that are not build inputs.
#
# Strategy: ALLOWLIST. Exclude everything, then re-include only the inputs the
# build actually needs. The build needs the Go module graph (go.mod/go.sum) and
# the Go packages under cmd/, internal/, and contracts/ (the last carries the
# go:embed'd schema JSONs — contracts/mcp/mcp-key-set.schema.json and the
# constraint schema under internal/profile — so it MUST be in the context or the
# embed fails to compile). There is nothing else the build reads. An allowlist
# cannot silently drift: a new top-level tree is excluded by default and only
# ships if it is explicitly re-included here.

# Exclude everything by default.
*

# Re-include the build inputs.
!go.mod
!go.sum
!cmd
!internal
!contracts
